      "body": "Thanks for the audit review.\n\n- Locale fragility: fixed in 9d0b0e2. All git subprocesses in `internal/gitutil` now go through a shared `newCmd` helper that appends `LC_ALL=C` and `LANG=C` to the inherited environment, so git stderr is always the English text the classifier matches regardless of the host locale. Added a unit test asserting the pinning wins over inherited `LC_ALL`/`LANG` on the constructed command.\n- Downstream blast radius (per-file isolation in `analyze.go`/`dependents.go`): deliberately deferred to a follow-up rather than expanded here \u2014 PR #39 is currently touching the analyze.go warning path and changing it in this PR would conflict. Filed as follow-up scope.\n- `\"not found\"` arm: kept as a defensive catch for older/other git versions where the phrasing differs, even if it is dead on modern git.",
