      "body": "## Audit re-review \u2014 head `9d0b0e2` (read-only, no changes)\n\nRe-checked after the locale pin landed. `go build` + `go test ./internal/gitutil/` green.\n\n**Resolved since the last pass:** the `LC_ALL=C`/`LANG=C` pin on the git subprocess (`internal/gitutil/git.go:462`) closes the locale-fragility I raised \u2014 and it's genuinely correct, not just cosmetic. Go's `os/exec` runs `dedupEnv` (keeps the **last** occurrence per key) before `execve` (`exec.go:1223`), so `append(os.Environ(), \"LC_ALL=C\", \"LANG=C\")` reaches git as a single `LC_ALL=C` even when the parent env already sets `LC_ALL`, on Linux and macOS alike. No need to strip existing vars first.\n\nRemaining:\n- **[Med]** The widened-blast-radius point from my earlier comment still stands (unaddressed): `internal/sem/analyze.go:33,39` and `dependents.go:65` `return \u2026, err` on `ShowFile`, so a single-file failure now aborts the whole `AnalyzeGitRange` / index build rather than being swallowed per-file as before. `analyze.go` already degrades hard *parse* failures to a warning + `continue`; worth a deliberate call on whether a transient single-file `ShowFile` error deserves the same per-file isolation. Design call, not a bug in this diff.\n- **[Nit]** `internal/gitutil/git.go:298` \u2014 the `\"not found\"` arm still looks dead for `git show REV:PATH`: across bad-rev / missing-path / on-disk-not-in-rev / bad-object I could reproduce only `does not exist` and `exists on disk, but not in`, never `not found`. Harmless, same spirit as the redundant `\"Path\"` clause this PR removed. *(speculative across git versions)*\n\n**Overall:** primary fix correct, locale concern now genuinely closed \u2014 safe to merge; the earlier blast-radius design call + one nit remain.\n",
