Payload:
Recommended tests belong beside the existing direct `compareEntities` cases in `internal/sem/analyze_test.go`; no additional helper is needed.

### 1. Duplicate inserted first

```go
func TestCompareEntitiesTrueDuplicateInsertedFirstOnlyAdded(t *testing.T) {
	before := []Entity{
		{Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F()", BodyHash: "h1", StartLine: 1},
		{Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F()", BodyHash: "h2", StartLine: 5},
	}
	after := []Entity{
		{Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F()", BodyHash: "h0", StartLine: 1},
		{Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F()", BodyHash: "h1", StartLine: 5},
		{Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F()", BodyHash: "h2", StartLine: 9},
	}

	changes, removed, added := compareEntities(before, after)
	if len(changes) != 0 || len(removed) != 0 {
		t.Fatalf("unexpected churn: changes=%#v removed=%#v", changes, removed)
	}
	if len(added) != 1 || added[0] != after[0] {
		t.Fatalf("added = %#v, want only inserted duplicate %#v", added, after[0])
	}
}
```

Current behavior is two phantom `body_changed` events and addition of `h2`, so asserting the entire added `Entity` is important.

### 2. Removal plus another overload’s signature edit

Use `Fingerprint` to make the intended continuity observable. `BodyHash` hashes the full block and normally changes with the declaration; for multiline entities, `Fingerprint` excludes the declaration line and survives a signature-only edit.

```go
func TestCompareEntitiesRemovalAndSignatureEditUseFingerprint(t *testing.T) {
	before := []Entity{
		{
			Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F(int)",
			BodyHash: "block-int", Fingerprint: "body-int", StartLine: 1,
		},
		{
			Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F(string)",
			BodyHash: "block-string-before", Fingerprint: "body-string", StartLine: 5,
		},
	}
	after := []Entity{
		{
			Kind: "method", Name: "C.F", Signature: "F(object)",
			BodyHash: "block-object-after", Fingerprint: "body-string", StartLine: 1,
		},
	}

	changes, removed, added := compareEntities(before, after)
	if len(added) != 0 {
		t.Fatalf("unexpected added: %#v", added)
	}
	if len(removed) != 1 || removed[0] != before[0] {
		t.Fatalf("removed = %#v, want only %#v", removed, before[0])
	}
	if len(changes) != 1 {
		t.Fatalf("changes = %#v, want one signature change", changes)
	}
	c := changes[0]
	if c.Type != "signature_changed" ||
		c.Kind != "method" || c.Name != "C.F" ||
		c.OldSignature != "F(string)" || c.NewSignature != "F(object)" ||
		c.BeforeStartLine != 5 || c.AfterStartLine != 1 {
		t.Fatalf("change = %#v, want F(string)->F(object), lines 5->1", c)
	}
}
```

Without `Fingerprint` or another continuity signal, this scenario is fundamentally ambiguous: `F(object)` is equally signature-similar to both prior overloads. Current code incorrectly pairs `F(int)->F(object)` and removes `F(string)` even when the fingerprint identifies the survivor.

Highest-value adjacent cases:

- Reorder true duplicates by body: `[h1,h2] -> [h2,h1]` should be inert. The existing reorder test uses distinct signatures and misses this path.
- Mirror removal: `[h0,h1,h2] -> [h1,h2]` should remove only `h0`.
- Exact signature must outrank shared fingerprints: before `F(int), F(string)` with identical fingerprints, after unchanged `F(string)`; remove only `F(int)`.
- Symmetric mixed operation: edit `F(int)->F(long)` using its fingerprint while removing `F(string)`.
- Fully indistinguishable duplicate insertion (`h1,h1 -> h1,h1,h1`): assert cardinality and no phantom changes, but not which line is “new.”
- Optional parser-backed C# coverage should use multiline methods so the fingerprint genuinely remains stable across a signature-only edit.

The focused pre-change `TestCompareEntities*` suite passed under the repository’s mise-managed Go 1.24 toolchain. I made no file edits.

